# Design system reference

## Shorthand

In prompts, **`/designsystem`** means: align with this project’s design system — the live doc and the HTML spec below. Use the same idea when the user says “design system”, “DS”, or “match the spec”.

## Where to look

| What | Where |
|------|--------|
| **Route (app)** | `/designsystem` — `ROUTES.designSystem` in `src/lib/constants/routes.ts` |
| **Local preview** | `http://localhost:5173/designsystem` (Vite dev default port) |
| **Canonical spec (source)** | `public/design-system-v2.html` (tokens, components, patterns, sections) |

Prefer the **HTML file** for exact class names, tokens, and structure. Use the **live route** to verify behaviour, scrolling, and layout in the browser.

## In Cursor

- Attach this rule with **`@design-system`** (or `@.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc`) when working on UI so the model keeps DS context.
- This rule applies when editing files matching `**/*.{tsx,css}`; for other files, still **@mention** this rule if styling or DS alignment matters.

## When implementing or reviewing UI

- Prefer existing DS tokens and patterns from `design-system-v2.html` over one-off colours/spacing.
- If the spec and the app disagree, call it out; the HTML doc is the documented contract unless product says otherwise.
